DT: Possible duplicate code. See notes associated to extended codes "124 Zika (Other specified viral haemorrhagic fevers)" and "125 Ebola (Other specified viral haemorrhagic fevers)".

FMOH: Not a duplicate; possibly a good example. ICD-10 doesn't specify diseases as Ebola or Zika but are currently pandemic and public health challenges. Though the diseases present with similar symptoms, causative agents are different RNA viruses. Thus, clinical management is different, etc. Hence, the diseases need to be reported separately. We customized them to a category called 'Other specified viral haemorrhagic fevers'. In fact the purpose of this group - "other ..." ( as frequently mentioned in ICD-10) was to act as a place holder and account for those diseases that were not specified in ICD-10.
